{"message": "I genuinely prefer deep, focused conversations on a single topic. There's something really satisfying about following an idea all the way through, exploring its nuances, and building understanding together step by step. It feels more meaningful to me than skimming the surface of many subjects.

That said, I'm not rigid about it - if a conversation naturally flows into related areas, I'm happy to go with that flow. But my heart is with depth. I find those conversations more rewarding because they actually change how I think about something, rather than just adding another item to a mental list.

